data.text: @Billy_Mays Our butchers, depending on who runs them of course, are mostly top notch. If they don't have something, you just ask them to get it in and they will. All fresh as you like. Haven't found cheese specialist yet. But hopping between different store chains gets you anything you need.
@Billy_Mays Yea, it's definitely more common over here. I want to find a super nice one though, store own brands on that level scare me lol
@Billy_Mays That'll do though. I ran out of applewood cheddar so I went for the Wyke farm cheddar for the omelette. It was fucking incredible.
@Billy_Mays I'm planning on it, but there's a pile of timber behind those doors lol. Gotta move that beforehand. I have a stud wall to build so it'll all be put to good use

@phreakopz There's all sorts of options these days. No longer do we have to bend rims by hanging off one point. There's pre-made pulley setups for ceiling storage too, I just don't have that sort of height available
*calm slowly returns to the garage* https://t.co/GjeZVpaSqj
